The article is a transcript of remarks made by Vice President Mike Pence and other officials during a visit to the Homeland Security Investigations Houston Field Office. Pence thanked the officials for their work in upholding the laws of the country and discussed the need for Congress to take action to address the immigration crisis at the southern border. He emphasized the importance of closing loopholes that human traffickers use to exploit vulnerable families and called for the construction of a border wall. Senator Ted Cruz and other officials also spoke about the urgency of addressing the crisis and the negative impact it has on communities and national security. Pence expressed hope that Mexico's recent efforts to address the issue will alleviate the need for tariffs or border closures, but emphasized that Congress must act to close the loopholes.